In [[Māori mythology|Māori tradition]], '''''Tūnui-ā-rangi''''' was one of the great [[Māori migration canoes|ocean-going, voyaging canoes]] (or [[Waka (canoe)|waka]]) that was used in the migrations that settled [[New Zealand]]. The waka is linked to the [[Ngāi Tāhuhu]] [[iwi]] from the [[Auckland Region|Auckland]] and [[Northland Region|Northland]] regions.

